

Brazil rocked Germany in three straight sets here on Saturday in 2006 women's volleyball World Championship.

It took Brazil 70 minutes to gain their eighth victory in the tournament with 25-16, 25-22 and 25-15.

Sheila Castro scored 11 points for Brazil while Welissa Gonzaga had 13 and Fabiana Claudino 10.

Captain Angelina Grun scored nine points to lead the Germany team, Birgit Thumm and Corina Ssuschke each contributed five points.

Brazil will face Russia on Sunday to decide the top team of the group. Both teams, who kept an unbeaten record in the tournament until now, had gained the berth for the semifinal.

